# Windsurf Rules — FOSS CVE Patching Boilerplate

Read `.agents/CONSTITUTION.md` first. All rules there apply here.

## This Repository
Managed fork of a FOSS project. Downloads official release archives (not git clone),
applies CVE security patches, compiles from source, ships patched container images.

## Key Rules
- Source build (`Dockerfile`) always has priority over `Dockerfile.binary`
- Version format: `{upstream_version}-r{N}` — e.g. `6.0.0-r1`
- Branch format: `release/6.0.0-r1`, `fix/CVE-2024-1234`
- Scripts stored as `.txt` extensions in repo: `build.sh.txt`, `scan.sh.txt`
- No secrets committed. No `latest` image tags.
- Every patch in `patches/` needs header: CVE, Upstream-PR, Keep-on-sync

